description: From Middle English whilende, whilwende, from Old English hwīlende, hwīlwende (“transitory, temporary, temporal”), from hwīl (“time, while”) + -wende (“moving, going about, turning”, suffix), equivalent to while +‎ wending.

adjectives.description: whilend (comparative more whilend, superlative most whilend)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) Passing; temporal; temporary; not lasting; not permanent; transient; transitory; not eternal.
